http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Visual Art Curriculum Standards for 3rd grade.
Media, Techniques, and Processes - Students will understand and apply media, techniques, and processes.
Use a variety of tools in a safe and responsible manner.
Use a variety of media.
Demonstrate and explain a variety of techniques.
Investigate and apply a variety of processes.
Recognize and demonstrate levels of craftsmanship.
Structures and Functions - Students will use knowledge of structures and functions.
Classify elements of art.
Apply elements of art.
Classify principles of design.
Apply principles of design.
Understand purpose in art.
Apply purpose in art.
Understand context in art.
Apply context in art.
Evaluation - Students will choose and evaluate a range of subject matter, symbols, and ideas.
Select and demonstrate subject matter, symbols, and ideas in one's own artwork.
Analyze and evaluate subject matter, symbols, and ideas in one's own artwork.
Explain subject matter, symbols, and ideas in artwork of others.
Historical and Cultural Relationships - The student will understand the visual arts in relation to history and cultures.
Understand and demonstrate that art comes from different cultures, times, and places.
Understand and demonstrate how culture, history, and art influence each other.
Reflecting and Assessing - The student will reflect upon and assess the characteristics and merits of their work and the work of others.
Analyze and discuss the characteristics and merits of one's own artwork.
Analyze and discuss the characteristics and merits of artworks of others.
Understand and demonstrate that viewers have different responses to art.
Interdisciplinary Connections - Students will make connections between visual arts and other disciplines.
Understand and discuss connections between visual arts and other arts disciplines.
Understand and discuss connections between visual arts and disciplines outside the arts.
